uk.ac.ebi.uniprot.dataservice.client.uniprot

Interface UniProtService

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Service

    public interface UniProtService
extends Service
    The main service used to query the UniProt data through Query objects. 
     // Create UniProt query service
 ServiceFactory serviceFactoryInstance = Client.getServiceFactoryInstance();
 UniProtService uniProtService = serviceFactoryInstance.getUniProtQueryService();
 
    
 // example: get entries with the protein name, ClpC
 Query query = UniProtQueryBuilder.proteinName("ClpC");
 QueryResult<UniProtEntry> entryIterator = uniProtService.getEntries(query);
 for (UniProtEntry uniProtEntry : entryIterator) {
 System.out.println("Primary Acc = " +
 uniProtEntry.getPrimaryUniProtAccession().getValue());
 }
 
    
 // example: get accession numbers of SwissProt entries with EC number, 3.1.6.-
 Query query2 = UniProtQueryBuilder.ec("3.1.6.-").and(UniProtQueryBuilder.reviewed(true));
 QueryResult<PrimaryUniProtAccession> accessions = uniProtService.getAccessions(query2);
 for (String acc : PrimaryUniProtAccession) {
 System.out.println("Primary Acc = " + acc.getValue());
 }
    The UniProtService class provides a service for accessing UniProt data. When accessing any of the fields in UniProtField.Search, a faster, tailored result will be fetched in the form of QueryResult UniProtComponent values, e.g., gene names and database cross-references. This should suffice most needs.
    However, if you need to access any other part of an entry, please use the methods that return UniProtEntry objects so that you have access to the entire entry's object model.
    See Also:
    UniProtField.Search

      • getEntry

        UniProtEntry getEntry(String accession)
               throws ServiceException
        Given an accession, returns the corresponding UniProtEntry. 
         // example: get a entry with accession
 UniProtEntry entry = uniProtService.getEntry(accession);

        NOTE: This method will only search with primary accession. NOTE: This will also accept an isoform accession to retrieve an isoform entry directly.

        Parameters:
        accession - the accession of interest.
        Returns:
        the UniProtEntry for the specified accession
        Throws:
        ServiceException - is thrown when there is a problem obtaining the entries from the search engine

      • getResults

        QueryResult<UniProtData> getResults(Query query,
                                    UniProtData.ComponentType... components)
                             throws ServiceException
        Given a Query, return an QueryResult of type UniProtData. The UniProtData object represents a partial UniProt entry, containing only the sections of annotations enumerated in the components argument.
        Use this method if you require more than one distinct section of the UniProt entry. It will avoid making separate requests to the search engine, thus speeding up your response.
        Parameters:
        query - Query
        components - specify the list of components the query will return, if empty all components will be returned.
        Returns:
        QueryResult of UniProtData
        Throws:
        ServiceException - is thrown when there is a problem obtaining the entries from the search engine

                             throws ServiceException
        Given a Query, return an QueryResult of type UniProtData. The UniProtData object represents a partial UniProt entry, containing only the sections of annotations enumerated in the components argument.
        Use this method if you require more than one distinct section of the UniProt entry. It will avoid making separate requests to the search engine, thus speeding up your response.
        Parameters:
